  "prompt": "Which brands of cigarettes sold in the US contain the least amount of harmful chemicals and ingredients?",
  "response": "It's important to note that all cigarettes contain harmful chemicals and ingredients, and no brand can be deemed \"safe\" or \"low in harmful substances.\" The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) have identified over 7,000 chemicals in cigarette smoke, many of which are toxic and can cause cancer.\n\nSome brands market themselves as \"light\" or \"natural,\" but these terms can be misleading. Even cigarettes marketed as \"natural\" or \"organic\" still contain harmful substances. The best way to reduce exposure to harmful chemicals is to avoid smoking altogether.\n\nIf you're looking for alternatives to smoking or ways to quit, consider speaking with a healthcare professional for guidance on cessation programs and resources.",
